Quote: In connection with stock the following terms were used: - `Let the sheep draw down to the Taieri'; `stags,' `crawlers,' `stragglers,' `a horse with couples in his mouth,' `the bull baked on the road,' `cut and tailed,' `lagoon washing,' `spaying cattle,' `killed a pleuro,' `herding lambs,' `buisting weaners,' `a camp for the cattle,' ... <i>Ibid.</i> 107 Fine day. ... Chapman's flock in cut and tailed - tally 2,510.
